    "created_at": "2014-01-01T00:52:06Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-01-01T00:53:05Z",
    "body": "Hm, would it be possible for the `SNAP` printing to be split out of `tidy` because the current output of `tidy` is extremely cluttered by the `NOTE: snapshot` printing, to the point that even experienced rustaceans will miss things like \"trailing whitespace\"?\n\ne.g. add a target `check-snaps` so `make check` runs `tidy`, `check-snaps`, etc. (This would also allow `check-snaps` to run `git grep SNAP -- '*.rs'` to filter down to just relevant lines and then process this reduced subset of lines in Python, which will be much faster than iterating over the entirety of each file in Python, and so probably won't be much slower than only doing one pass (as is currently implemented).)\n",
